    Running the read, validate and preprocess

    run_seahtrue.Rd

    This function takes the Seahorse Wave excel file and computes it through read, validate and preprocess

    Usage

    run_seahtrue(filepath_seahorse, ...)

    Arguments

    filepath_seahorse

    Absolute path to the Seahorse Excel file.

    ...

    Dots argument (…) allows the function to take an undefined number of arguments.

    Value

    A preprocessed seahorse dataset is returned as an output. This is a nested tibble with the following 7 columns:

    * plate_id = Barcode from the 'Assay Configuration' sheet from the Seahorse Excel file.

    * filepath_seahorse = Path to Seahorse Excel file.

    * date = Date derived from 'Assay Configuration' sheet of the Seahorse Excel file.

    * assay_info = Dataframe with information from the 'Assay Configuration' sheet from the Seahorse Excel file.

    * injection_info = Dataframe with information derived from 'Operation log' sheet.

    * raw_data = Preprocessed raw dataframe from Seahorse 'Raw' sheet.

    * rate_data = Preprocessed rate data from 'Rate' sheet.

    Examples

    run_seahtrue(system.file("extdata", "20191219_SciRep_PBMCs_donor_A.xlsx", package = "seahtrue"))
